{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/composite-layers/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"DERMECK'S Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f16bbb23-e02c-5e01-b06e-e252e1377f57","excerpt":"While rendering the browser paints the elements on potentientally more than one layer. Those are composed into the final image that is drawn to the screen. In…","html":"<p>While rendering the browser paints the elements on potentientally more than one layer. Those are composed into the final image that is drawn to the screen.</p>\n<p>In the Chrome DevTools those layers can be inspected.</p>\n<h2>Show Layer Borders in Rendering Tab</h2>\n<p>Go to <code class=\"language-text\">Chrome &gt; More tools &gt; Rendering</code>. Here you can select <code class=\"language-text\">Layer Borders</code> which will … well draw borders around the layers on the screen.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/c2d13/mozilla-layer-borders.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.06329113924051%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Layers Tab\"\n        title=\"Layers Tab\"\n        src=\"/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/f058b/mozilla-layer-borders.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/c26ae/mozilla-layer-borders.png 158w,\n/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/6bdcf/mozilla-layer-borders.png 315w,\n/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/f058b/mozilla-layer-borders.png 630w,\n/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/40601/mozilla-layer-borders.png 945w,\n/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/78612/mozilla-layer-borders.png 1260w,\n/static/6ddee0c5e645512ce98277fe5f491c0f/c2d13/mozilla-layer-borders.png 2560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Analyze Layers in Performance Tab</h2>\n<p>To analyze the layers in the Chrome Performance Tab you first have to activate <code class=\"language-text\">enable advanced paint instrumentation</code> in the <a href=\"https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/evaluate-performance/reference/#settings\">Recording Settings</a> - those can be found when clicking the gear icon in the Performance Tab.</p>\n<p>Now you can record a Performance Snapshot as usual. When analyzing the profile you can select a certain frame and inspect the corresponding layer information in the Layers Tab.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/c2d13/mozilla-layers.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.06329113924051%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Layers Tab\"\n        title=\"Layers Tab\"\n        src=\"/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/f058b/mozilla-layers.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/c26ae/mozilla-layers.png 158w,\n/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/6bdcf/mozilla-layers.png 315w,\n/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/f058b/mozilla-layers.png 630w,\n/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/40601/mozilla-layers.png 945w,\n/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/78612/mozilla-layers.png 1260w,\n/static/751ad9c451aa2d1b90917b5bf580df80/c2d13/mozilla-layers.png 2560w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Show Composite Layers In Chrome DevTools","date":"August 23, 2021","description":"How to show Composite Layers in the Chrome DevTools"}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/website-to-desktop-app/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Turn Websites into \"Desktop Apps\" with Chrome Shortcuts"}},"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"f16bbb23-e02c-5e01-b06e-e252e1377f57","previousPostId":"a5e42211-c0ee-5087-b666-5f1568308281","nextPostId":null}},"staticQueryHashes":["3000541721","3274528899"]}